If the table is missing, hasTable resolves to false.
```
import { SimpleDB } from '@nshiab/simple-data-analysis';
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
const exists = await sdb.hasTable('nonexistent_table');
if (!exists) {
  console.log('Table does not exist.');
} else {
  console.log('Table exists.');
}
await sdb.done();
```

Yes, you can call it anytime after tables are created.
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// We create a new table
const table = sdb.newTable("employees");
// Log all table names to the console
await sdb.logTableNames();
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

