```

Here's how you can retrieve all tables in the database:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// We create a new table
const table = sdb.newTable();
// We get all tables
const tables = await sdb.getTables();
// We log the number of tables
console.log(`Number of tables: ${tables.length}`);
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

You can specify the table name when creating it. Here's an example:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Create a table with a specific name
const myTable = sdb.newTable("myDataTable");
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

Set the `logDuration` flag when creating the instance:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
const sdb = new SimpleDB({
  logDuration: true,
});
await sdb.done();
```

You can use the `getTableNames` method to retrieve an array of all table names. Here's how:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Get all table names
const tableNames = await sdb.getTableNames();
console.log(tableNames);
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

Use the `getTables` method to retrieve an array of all tables. Here's how:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Create some tables for demonstration
sdb.newTable("customers");
sdb.newTable("orders");
// Get all table instances
const tablesArray = await sdb.getTables();
console.log("Number of tables:", tablesArray.length);
console.log("First table in array:", tablesArray[0]);
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

Here’s how to check if a specific table exists in the database:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
const tableNames = await sdb.getTableNames();
const tableToCheck = "orders";
const exists = tableNames.includes(tableToCheck);
console.log(`Table ${tableToCheck} exists: ${exists}`);
await sdb.done();
```

After retrieving the names, load data into each table using `loadData`:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
const tableNames = await sdb.getTableNames();
for (const name of tableNames) {
  const table = sdb.newTable(name);
  await table.loadData(`./data/${name}.csv`);
  console.log(`Loaded data into ${name}`);
}
await sdb.done();
```
